@X3Finance @sjwill99 @lesigh3100 @Uniswap This answer is incorrect.

"Leverage is an investment strategy of using borrowed money to increase the potential return of an investment." (investopedia)

Leverage means you can lose more than you put in. That's not the case for Uni V3

@X3Finance @sjwill99 @lesigh3100 @Uniswap You cannot create a leveraged position in Uniswap, so max IL is the same regardless of the range of the position in Unit V3.

And IL is not a real loss, in the sense that got cannot offset other gains from a tax perspective. See below:
https://t.co/HUgSFSV1lh

@0xdoug How low is low vol regimes?

The max fee on Uniswap is 1%. The implied volatility needs to be less than ~19% for the daily 1sd expected to be less than 1%. 

Most crypto assets have IV&gt;75%, so even the 1% pool will see trading activity every day if there's enough liquidity

